{{ja-kanjitab|yomi=k|え}}

{{IPAchar|/je/}} → {{IPAchar|/e/}}

From {{inh|ja|ojp|sort=え|-}}. The ''ye'' pronunciation gradually dropped out in {{w|Early Middle Japanese}}, persisting in some dialects and specific terms.  For instance, see {{pedialite|Yebisu}}

This term was so representative of the ''ye'' reading that it lent its shape to the {{w|hentaigana}} {{m|ja|𛀁|tr=ye}}.

